34 And just as, by natural instinct,
35 the magpies together, at the beginning of day,
36 move to warm their cold feathers;

37 then some go away without returning,
38 others turn back to where they were stirred,
39 and others hover, wheeling around;

52 And I began: “My merit
53 does not make me worthy of your reply;
54 but for her who grants me to ask it,

55 blessed life that you remain hidden
56 within your joy, make known to me
57 the reason that has placed you so near to me;

64 Down the steps of the holy stairway
65 I descended only to do you honor
66 with speech and with the light that cloaks me;

73 “I see well,” I said, “sacred lamp,
74 how free love in this court
75 suffices to follow eternal providence;

79 Nor had I come to the last word,
80 when the light made its center of its middle,
81 spinning like a swift millstone;

88 From here comes the joy with which I flame;
89 for to my sight, as clear as it is,
90 I match the brightness of the flame.

100 The mind, which shines here, smokes on earth;
101 therefore consider how it can down there
102 grasp that which it could not because heaven exalts it”.

112 Thus the third spirit began again to speak to me;
113 and then, continuing, he said: “There
114 I made myself so steadfast in the service of God,

118 That cloister used to render fertilely to these heavens;
119 and now it has become empty,
120 so that it must soon be revealed.

139 They came around this one and stopped,
140 and uttered a cry of such a high pitch
141 that it could not be likened to anything here;
